3.1b
informative speech is a speech that keeps the audiencee interested and presents knowledge in a simple enough way.

four types of informative speeches:
- definitional speeches: show topic that the audience is not familiar with
- descriptive speeches: show a topic so that the audience can visualise it
- explanatory speech: show why something is the way we present it
- demonstration speech: show the audience how something is done

3.1c
- moving objects
- storytelling: people like hearing stories in general so they will be more interested in presentation
- contrasts
- comparisons
